quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  28,85,"He who ordained the Qur'an for you [Prophet] will see you back to your destination. Say, \"My Lord best knows he who brought true guidance, and he who is clearly lost"
  28,86,"You [Prophet] could not have expected that the Book would be conveyed to you, but [It is] a mercy from your Lord. So do not back up the unbelievers"
  28,87,"and never let them turn you away from God's revelations after they have been revealed to you. [Instead], invite people to your Lord. Never be one of those who associate others with God"
  28,88,"and do not invoke another god besides God; there is no god except Him. All things will perish except His Face. Judgment belongs to Him, and to Him you will be returned"
  29,1,Alif Lam Meem
  29,2,"do people think that they will be left to say, \"We believe,\" without being tested"
  29,3,"We have tested those who lived before them, so God will note those who prove to be truthful, and will note the liars"
  29,4,"Or do those who do bad deeds think they can escape Us? [That is] bad judgment on their part"
  29,5,"As for those who look forward to meeting God, God's appointed time is coming. He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing"
  29,6,"And whoever strives, strives only to benefit himself, for God is rich beyond any needs of the worlds"